code: library(terra) tun_ext <- ext(6, 12, 30, 38) r_tun <- rast(tun_ext, res = 0.1, crs = "EPSG:4326") wkt_lines <- c(   "LINESTRING (9.0 36.0, 9.5 35.0, 10.0 34.5)",   "LINESTRING (8.5 33.5, 9.0 33.0, 10.0 32.5)" ) water_sv <- vect(data.frame(wkt = wkt_lines),                  geom = "wkt",                  crs  = "EPSG:4326") water_sv$water <- 1 water_rast <- rasterize(   water_sv,   r_tun,   field      = "water",   background = 0   ) plot(water_rast, main = "Example watercourses") plot(tunisia, add = TRUE, color = "red") ri_water <- augment_epi_units_with_raster(   epi_units = tunisia,    raster = water_rast,    risk_name = "water_risk",    aggregate_fun = "mean" ) |>    rescale_risk_scores(     cols = "water_risk",      from = c(0,1),     to = c(0,100),      method = "quadratic"   )  ggplot(ri_water) +   geom_sf(aes(fill = water_risk)) +   scale_fill_viridis_c(limits = c(0, 100)) ri_random <- tunisia |>    select(my_key = eu_id) |>    mutate(     ri_random = runif(nrow(tunisia), min = 0, max = 100)          ) |>    filter(row_number() <= 30) |>    rescale_risk_scores(     cols = "ri_random",     from = c(0, 100), to = c(0, 100), method = "sigmoid"   )

what: Build the weighted emission risk table — calc_emission_risk
title: Build the weighted emission risk table — calc_emission_risk
text: function calculates overall emission risk score (emission_risk) set countries based four domains (one counts certain number points towards risk introduction 12 default) : Epidemiological status (3/12):  Time since last outbreak (sc_epistatus). Surveillance measures (2/12): Effectiveness implemented surveillance strategies (sc_survmeasures). Control measures (3/12): Effectiveness disease control measures (sc_control). Animal commerce movements (4/12): Risk commerce movement animals (sc_commerce). emission risk sum . scores calculated emission risk factors weighted based emission risk factor weights (weights parameter). sc_epistatus: epidemiological status score based time since last outbreak accounds 3 12 final emission risk score. disease detected last 5 years (\(x > 5\)), score 0. disease currently present (\(x = 0\)), score 3. exponential decay model smooths scoring time: $$S = 3 \times \exp\left(-x \frac{\log(2)}{5}\right)$$ sc_survmeasures: Surveillance measures scored based absence effective measures accounts 2 12 og final emission risk score. following risk factors contribute score: Active surveillance Passive surveillance Risk-based surveillance Mandatory reporting sc_control: Control measures scored similarly, account 3 12 emission risk score. following risk factors contribute score: Border control Culling outbreak sites Culling around outbreak sites Movement zoning restrictions Ring vaccination around outbreak sites sc_commerce: risk score animal commerce movements can take values 0, 1, 3, 4. sum following: 0 means legal illegal trade legal trade present adds 1 score illegal trade present adds 3 score overall emission risk score sum weighted risk factor, final emission risk score range (0, 12].

title: Scaling range transformation function (re-scaling) — rescale_risk_scores
text: dataset dataset add scaled risk column . cols Column containing numeric vector risk values range [0, 12] named vector, names used names_to arg, giving new names rescaled columns. existing range possible values risk_col converted new range possible values risk_col, default 0 100. method scaling method apply. Options "linear", "quadratic", "exponential", "sigmoid", "complementary". inverse boolean inverse risk values, .e. low becomes high, high becomes low. Similar "complementary" value method, can added quadratic. names_prefix string, prefix cols names new names scaled columns. names_to string vector, provide new name rescaled columns. keep_cols default TRUE, whether keep cols columns rescaling done remove.

title: Scaling range transformation function (re-scaling) — rescale_risk_scores
text: dataset new column containing  numeric vector scaled values range [0, 100].

title: Scaling range transformation function (re-scaling) — rescale_risk_scores
text: equations used method: Linear Scaling $$f(x) = \frac{x - 0}{12 - 0} \cdot (100 - 0) + 0$$ Quadratic Scaling $$f(x) = \left(\frac{x - 0}{12 - 0}\right)^2 \cdot (100 - 0) + 0$$ Exponential Scaling $$f(x) = \frac{\exp(x / 12) - 1}{\exp(1) - 1} \cdot (100 - 0) + 0$$ Sigmoid Scaling $$f(x) = \frac{100}{1 + \exp(-10 \cdot (\frac{x}{12} - 0.5))}$$
